1
00:01:40,220 --> 00:01:44,210
[A Moment But Forever]

2
00:01:45,060 --> 00:01:47,160
[Episode 19]

3
00:01:50,280 --> 00:01:51,870
What is this thing for?

4
00:01:52,430 --> 00:01:54,350
This? It's an iron chisel.

5
00:01:54,950 --> 00:01:55,789
How do you use it?

6
00:01:57,560 --> 00:01:58,789
The iron chisel is used like this.

7
00:02:00,900 --> 00:02:01,950
May I try it?

8
00:02:02,590 --> 00:02:03,400
Sure.

9
00:02:03,840 --> 00:02:04,640
Thank you.

10
00:02:05,640 --> 00:02:06,640
It's just a piece of iron.

11
00:02:06,640 --> 00:02:07,920
What's so interesting about it?

12
00:02:08,520 --> 00:02:09,310
Madam.

13
00:02:12,400 --> 00:02:13,190
Tanyin.

14
00:02:13,680 --> 00:02:15,360
This cabinet you made is really beautiful.

15
00:02:15,680 --> 00:02:16,520
You have very dexterous hands.

16
00:02:19,870 --> 00:02:20,710
This Pei Jiu,

17
00:02:20,710 --> 00:02:22,360
he was supposed to come and try on his wedding outfit.

18
00:02:22,380 --> 00:02:24,130
It's already past noon, and there's still no sign of him.

19
00:02:24,430 --> 00:02:26,400
I bet that muddlehead forgot again.

20
00:02:27,630 --> 00:02:28,430
Qian Lin.

21
00:02:28,829 --> 00:02:29,829
Do me a small favor

22
00:02:29,960 --> 00:02:31,450
and try on the wedding outfit for Pei Jiu.

23
00:02:31,520 --> 00:02:32,240
Me?

24
00:02:32,960 --> 00:02:33,910
Try on the wedding outfit?

25
00:02:33,960 --> 00:02:35,079
Yes, you.

26
00:02:35,430 --> 00:02:36,420
You carry on, Tanyin.

27
00:02:36,490 --> 00:02:37,300
Let's go, let's go.

28
00:02:38,150 --> 00:02:39,400
I'll go with you.

29
00:02:45,190 --> 00:02:46,680
It fits you quite well.

30
00:02:46,860 --> 00:02:47,680
Then, won't it be

31
00:02:47,680 --> 00:02:49,000
a bit too large for Pei Jiu?

32
00:02:49,910 --> 00:02:51,150
Turn around and let me see.

33
00:02:52,690 --> 00:02:53,530
Turn this way.

34
00:02:57,760 --> 00:02:58,800
He's taller than Pei Jiu.

35
00:02:58,820 --> 00:03:00,500
Then the length should be fine, right?

36
00:03:00,810 --> 00:03:02,690
The length seems fine.

37
00:03:04,080 --> 00:03:04,800
But if the shoulders

38
00:03:04,800 --> 00:03:06,190
could be taken in a bit,

39
00:03:06,210 --> 00:03:07,280
it would be more suitable

40
00:03:07,280 --> 00:03:08,400
for Pei Jiu.

41
00:03:09,130 --> 00:03:10,180
I think so too.

42
00:03:11,010 --> 00:03:12,970
He looks quite good in this wedding attire.

43
00:03:15,070 --> 00:03:17,070
Isn't he fairer than Pei Jiu?

44
00:03:19,840 --> 00:03:20,870
Fairer?

45
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:22,400
I think they look about the same.

46
00:03:22,470 --> 00:03:23,400
About the same?

47
00:03:23,510 --> 00:03:24,950
Why do I feel he's much fairer?

48
00:03:25,560 --> 00:03:27,370
Can you just focus on the outfit?

49
00:03:28,030 --> 00:03:29,000
Stand still and don't move around.

50
00:03:30,290 --> 00:03:31,329
Alright, that should be enough.

51
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:32,240
Let's leave it at that.

52
00:03:32,240 --> 00:03:32,960
Wait a moment.

53
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:35,190
The hat.

54
00:03:35,430 --> 00:03:36,520
I was just teasing Pei Jiu for being forgetful,

55
00:03:36,520 --> 00:03:37,800
but mine is just as bad.

56
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:38,590
I forgot to bring the hat.

57
00:03:38,590 --> 00:03:39,520
Wait here. I'll go get it.

58
00:03:40,630 --> 00:03:41,470
In a moment!

59
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:55,910
How old are you?

60
00:03:56,470 --> 00:03:57,280
"How old are you?"

61
00:03:58,280 --> 00:04:00,030
Only children are asked such questions.

62
00:04:00,030 --> 00:04:01,470
Aren't you just a child?

63
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:03,150
I bet you're not even married yet.

64
00:04:03,150 --> 00:04:04,030
I'm not young at all.

65
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:05,310
At my age,

66
00:04:05,310 --> 00:04:06,400
if I were living in my clan,

67
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:07,490
I'd have several children by now.

68
00:04:08,130 --> 00:04:08,710
I...

69
00:04:09,260 --> 00:04:10,740
I just wanted to wait a bit longer.

70
00:04:12,860 --> 00:04:13,580
I really wouldn't have guessed

71
00:04:13,600 --> 00:04:15,120
that you come from a big family.

72
00:04:15,470 --> 00:04:16,560
Where is your home?

73
00:04:20,920 --> 00:04:22,000
A place far away.

74
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:24,190
You don't want to say it?

75
00:04:24,360 --> 00:04:25,160
It's okay.

76
00:04:25,390 --> 00:04:26,800
You don't have to say if you don't want to.

77
00:04:28,480 --> 00:04:30,040
My home is also far away.

78
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:32,560
Probably even farther than yours.

79
00:04:33,190 --> 00:04:34,270
I don't want to talk about it either.

80
00:04:53,120 --> 00:04:55,120
What exactly is your relationship

81
00:04:55,510 --> 00:04:56,800
with that Mr. Yuan?

82
00:04:58,070 --> 00:04:59,000
Master and servant, I suppose.

83
00:05:00,630 --> 00:05:01,430
If,

84
00:05:01,430 --> 00:05:02,430
I mean if,

85
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:04,240
if he were in danger,

86
00:05:05,120 --> 00:05:08,360
would you be... sad and upset?

87
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:09,830
In danger?

88
00:05:13,440 --> 00:05:16,050
Like what happened on the tower ship before.

89
00:05:16,480 --> 00:05:18,390
If he were to get hurt...

90
00:05:18,750 --> 00:05:19,550
If he...

91
00:05:23,630 --> 00:05:24,430
Then...

92
00:05:24,600 --> 00:05:26,240
then I would definitely protect him.

93
00:05:28,940 --> 00:05:31,390
[Yesterday's Inn]

94
00:05:52,240 --> 00:05:53,510
You're still up so late?

95
00:05:54,159 --> 00:05:54,830
I'm not tired.

96
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:56,630
I see you've been busy all along.

97
00:05:57,159 --> 00:05:58,000
Have some water.

98
00:06:00,120 --> 00:06:01,480
It's clean. I haven't used it.

99
00:06:02,760 --> 00:06:03,430
Thank you.

100
00:06:03,920 --> 00:06:05,600
No, I should be the one thanking you.

101
00:06:05,830 --> 00:06:06,830
You saved my life.

102
00:06:06,920 --> 00:06:08,560
You've already thanked me many times for it.

103
00:06:08,950 --> 00:06:10,560
Then let me thank you once more.

104
00:06:22,950 --> 00:06:25,040
You seem... upset.

105
00:06:25,120 --> 00:06:25,830
How can you tell

106
00:06:25,830 --> 00:06:26,830
that I'm upset?

107
00:06:27,520 --> 00:06:29,310
Earlier, I wasn't completely unconscious

108
00:06:29,340 --> 00:06:30,630
when I was in a coma.

109
00:06:30,870 --> 00:06:32,390
I vaguely saw you.

110
00:06:32,950 --> 00:06:33,950
At that time,

111
00:06:34,070 --> 00:06:35,630
your smile was far more genuine than it is now.

112
00:06:42,510 --> 00:06:43,600
What's making you upset?

113
00:06:43,870 --> 00:06:45,800
Would you like to talk about it?

114
00:06:47,190 --> 00:06:48,270
I have a friend.

115
00:06:49,360 --> 00:06:50,830
She has a very good male friend.

116
00:06:51,480 --> 00:06:53,270
But for some reason,

117
00:06:53,270 --> 00:06:54,310
he seems to be angry.

118
00:06:54,600 --> 00:06:56,040
Even though he's clearly in the room,

119
00:06:57,120 --> 00:06:58,390
he pretends not to be there

120
00:06:58,720 --> 00:06:59,920
and won't let her in.

121
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:01,800
It seems like

122
00:07:02,020 --> 00:07:03,340
he's deliberately avoiding her.

123
00:07:08,240 --> 00:07:10,870
Did they... have a fight?

124
00:07:12,040 --> 00:07:12,830
A fight?

125
00:07:16,270 --> 00:07:17,070
No, they didn't.

126
00:07:17,680 --> 00:07:18,600
Some people

127
00:07:18,660 --> 00:07:19,690
are just like that.

128
00:07:19,840 --> 00:07:21,840
Moody and ruthless.

129
00:07:22,510 --> 00:07:23,430
They can't change.

130
00:07:23,750 --> 00:07:24,750
It's their nature.

131
00:07:25,190 --> 00:07:26,360
That's not true at all.

132
00:07:27,270 --> 00:07:28,430
I think it is.

133
00:07:28,750 --> 00:07:29,920
Go tell that friend of yours

134
00:07:30,040 --> 00:07:30,870
to be careful.

135
00:07:31,680 --> 00:07:32,470
Or maybe...

136
00:07:33,560 --> 00:07:34,690
you should find a new friend instead.

137
00:07:37,270 --> 00:07:38,390
Forget it. Let's not talk about it anymore.

138
00:07:38,390 --> 00:07:39,600
You wouldn't understand anyway.

139
00:07:47,050 --> 00:07:48,970
Where did all these chicken feathers come from?

140
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:50,600
Did a weasel get in?

141
00:07:53,120 --> 00:07:53,800
Hello, Jiu.

142
00:07:55,480 --> 00:07:56,510
You're sweeping, Liu.

143
00:07:57,430 --> 00:07:58,560
What good stuff are you holding?

144
00:08:00,270 --> 00:08:01,070
It's a secret.

145
00:08:01,680 --> 00:08:02,480
Go away, go away.

146
00:08:04,280 --> 00:08:05,280
Who's Liu?

147
00:08:06,380 --> 00:08:06,960
Yunniang.

148
00:08:08,950 --> 00:08:09,800
Why are you here?

149
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:10,720
Aren't you busy today?

150
00:08:10,870 --> 00:08:12,310
Of course, I'm busy.

151
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:14,560
But no matter how busy I am, I have to prioritize what's important.

152
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:15,110
Look.

153
00:08:16,630 --> 00:08:17,560
Didn't you say

154
00:08:17,630 --> 00:08:18,750
you wanted to follow the old tradition

155
00:08:18,750 --> 00:08:20,240
of setting off fireworks the night before the wedding?

156
00:08:20,980 --> 00:08:21,940
I brought some for you.

157
00:08:22,750 --> 00:08:23,950
Quick, get me a bowl of water.

158
00:08:26,360 --> 00:08:28,160
Why make such a fuss over these few things?

159
00:08:29,070 --> 00:08:29,920
Don't get me started.

160
00:08:30,040 --> 00:08:31,480
Just now, I don't know why,

161
00:08:32,150 --> 00:08:32,870
but I couldn't find

162
00:08:32,870 --> 00:08:34,360
the way to your inn.

163
00:08:36,150 --> 00:08:37,200
Were you going in circles?

164
00:08:37,320 --> 00:08:38,120
No.

165
00:08:40,549 --> 00:08:41,909
I was just wandering around,

166
00:08:41,909 --> 00:08:43,080
unable to remember how to get here.

167
00:08:43,630 --> 00:08:44,720
Lately,

168
00:08:44,750 --> 00:08:46,240
things have been quite strange for me.

169
00:08:46,390 --> 00:08:47,390
I can't sleep well at night,

170
00:08:47,610 --> 00:08:48,300
and when I do sleep,

171
00:08:48,320 --> 00:08:49,610
I keep having lots of dreams.

172
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:51,270
They feel like they're about someone else's life

173
00:08:51,920 --> 00:08:53,070
or maybe from my past life.

174
00:08:53,320 --> 00:08:55,120
But when I wake up, I can't remember any of it.

175
00:08:56,150 --> 00:08:57,720
I've been worried about forgetting things lately.

176
00:08:57,910 --> 00:08:58,720
Look.

177
00:08:59,240 --> 00:09:00,000
Now, I write everything

178
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:01,550
down in this little notebook.

179
00:09:02,250 --> 00:09:02,940
Look.

180
00:09:03,670 --> 00:09:04,480
The last one.

181
00:09:04,790 --> 00:09:06,480
"Sending fireworks to Yunniang."

182
00:09:08,960 --> 00:09:10,390
If it weren't for this note,

183
00:09:10,600 --> 00:09:12,390
I'm afraid I would have forgotten about this entirely.

184
00:09:14,750 --> 00:09:15,390
Oh, right.

185
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:21,790
Yunniang,

186
00:09:22,160 --> 00:09:24,160
take a look at it and see if you like it.

187
00:09:30,480 --> 00:09:31,600
Such a precious thing.

188
00:09:31,630 --> 00:09:32,790
Where did you get it?

189
00:09:32,790 --> 00:09:33,600
Well, I

190
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:35,720
saved money for a long time

191
00:09:36,070 --> 00:09:37,340
to buy

192
00:09:37,870 --> 00:09:39,270
the only pearl necklace in town.

193
00:09:44,870 --> 00:09:45,670
And this.

194
00:09:46,630 --> 00:09:48,270
We're getting married the day after tomorrow.

195
00:09:48,770 --> 00:09:49,890
I'll leave this little notebook

196
00:09:50,080 --> 00:09:51,630
with you for safekeeping.

197
00:09:52,030 --> 00:09:53,240
It's now like

198
00:09:53,240 --> 00:09:54,360
half my life to me.

199
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:55,750
I'm afraid

200
00:09:55,750 --> 00:09:56,960
I might forget it too in the future.

201
00:09:57,270 --> 00:09:58,480
I'll feel at ease leaving it with you.

202
00:10:03,320 --> 00:10:05,150
You're not afraid of forgetting me too, huh?

203
00:10:05,750 --> 00:10:07,030
What are you talking about?

204
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:08,440
Even if I forget myself,

205
00:10:08,440 --> 00:10:09,550
I could never forget you.

206
00:10:16,950 --> 00:10:18,030
Greetings, Young Mistress.

207
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:20,200
How is his injury?

208
00:10:20,670 --> 00:10:21,630
Not good.

209
00:10:22,320 --> 00:10:23,200
Has he regained consciousness?

210
00:10:42,960 --> 00:10:43,750
Tanghua?

211
00:10:46,480 --> 00:10:47,270
Tanghua.

212
00:11:21,960 --> 00:11:25,330
♫I gaze into your deep eyes♫

213
00:11:26,310 --> 00:11:29,590
♫For whom do you take apart the word "love"?♫

214
00:11:31,780 --> 00:11:35,080
♫Turning around, it's like a dream♫

215
00:11:33,360 --> 00:11:34,150
Let me do it.

216
00:11:37,180 --> 00:11:41,290
♫I have betrayed deep love♫

217
00:11:42,260 --> 00:11:43,570
Go fetch a plum candy.

218
00:11:43,580 --> 00:11:47,430
♫Heaving a long, helpless sigh♫

219
00:11:44,150 --> 00:11:44,910
Mr. Tanghua

220
00:11:44,910 --> 00:11:46,510
can't even swallow medicine right now.

221
00:11:46,600 --> 00:11:48,080
How could he possibly eat candy?

222
00:11:48,250 --> 00:11:52,170
♫Time flies too rapidly♫

223
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:51,000
It's for me.

224
00:11:52,670 --> 00:11:53,480
Yes, Young Mistress.

225
00:11:54,460 --> 00:11:58,120
♫Life is like a flying bird♫

226
00:11:58,710 --> 00:12:03,600
♫Joining, scattering, no way back♫

227
00:12:04,710 --> 00:12:07,850
♫Unable to get what I yearn for, I sink in sadness♫

228
00:12:10,070 --> 00:12:14,210
♫When I brush past love, fate is set♫

229
00:12:15,070 --> 00:12:17,610
♫I've used up my brush and ink♫

230
00:12:17,900 --> 00:12:21,110
♫I couldn't describe♫

231
00:12:21,200 --> 00:12:25,490
♫This lovesick path♫

232
00:12:27,240 --> 00:12:28,910
Yunniang, why are you here?

233
00:12:29,240 --> 00:12:30,440
Are you here to check on the furniture?

234
00:12:31,080 --> 00:12:31,870
Not at all.

235
00:12:31,870 --> 00:12:33,270
I trust your craftsmanship.

236
00:12:33,960 --> 00:12:35,030
Then why are you here?

237
00:12:36,240 --> 00:12:37,270
I'm here to drop this off.

238
00:12:39,150 --> 00:12:39,960
What's wrong with it?

239
00:12:41,750 --> 00:12:43,200
Originally, we only needed one box of fireworks.

240
00:12:43,390 --> 00:12:44,270
But Pei Jiu actually forgot

241
00:12:44,270 --> 00:12:45,360
that he had already sent one two days ago

242
00:12:45,420 --> 00:12:46,420
and sent another box today.

243
00:12:47,440 --> 00:12:48,630
Pei Jiu is not himself today.

244
00:12:48,870 --> 00:12:50,480
His memory shouldn't be this poor.

245
00:12:50,870 --> 00:12:52,750
Is he... is he sick?

246
00:12:53,670 --> 00:12:55,120
At first, I thought so too.

247
00:12:55,150 --> 00:12:56,510
But after thinking it over,

248
00:12:56,550 --> 00:12:57,710
that doesn't seem to be the case.

249
00:12:58,270 --> 00:12:59,240
This memory problem of his

250
00:12:59,440 --> 00:13:00,750
seems to have started when he began learning martial arts

251
00:13:00,750 --> 00:13:01,910
from your young master.

252
00:13:04,790 --> 00:13:06,870
Tanyin, I don't think of you as an outsider.

253
00:13:07,590 --> 00:13:08,760
I won't beat around the bush.

254
00:13:08,840 --> 00:13:10,440
Could you ask your young master

255
00:13:10,630 --> 00:13:11,550
if Pei Jiu's condition

256
00:13:11,960 --> 00:13:13,550
has anything to do with learning martial arts?

257
00:13:13,790 --> 00:13:15,150
I'm really worried about him.

258
00:13:23,150 --> 00:13:23,870
Do you think

259
00:13:23,870 --> 00:13:25,510
once Pei Jiu regains his memories,

260
00:13:25,510 --> 00:13:27,080
his personally will completely change?

261
00:13:27,790 --> 00:13:28,750
I wonder if the proprietress

262
00:13:28,750 --> 00:13:30,440
will still like him.

263
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:31,790
Can they

264
00:13:31,790 --> 00:13:33,240
still be together happily?

265
00:13:33,670 --> 00:13:34,750
Recently,

266
00:13:34,750 --> 00:13:36,030
my memory has been poor.

267
00:13:36,210 --> 00:13:37,940
Look at my brain.

268
00:13:38,200 --> 00:13:40,320
When I went to the government office today,

269
00:13:41,040 --> 00:13:43,760
I couldn't even remember what the magistrate looked like.

270
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:29,320
The town hasn't been peaceful lately.

271
00:14:29,560 --> 00:14:30,320
Near the abandoned temple,

272
00:14:30,350 --> 00:14:31,960
several young beggars have gone missing.

273
00:16:08,360 --> 00:16:13,110
[Yesterday's Inn]

274
00:16:43,240 --> 00:16:44,030
Master,

275
00:16:44,510 --> 00:16:45,360
why do I always feel that something is missing

276
00:16:45,360 --> 00:16:46,600
when I use my spiritual power

277
00:16:47,910 --> 00:16:49,320
to break through my Spirit Courtyard?

278
00:16:50,870 --> 00:16:52,120
Did you...

279
00:16:52,240 --> 00:16:53,240
What do you want to say?

280
00:16:55,450 --> 00:16:56,480
Hold something back?

281
00:16:57,630 --> 00:16:58,750
When we first started teaching you,

282
00:16:58,750 --> 00:16:59,960
you acted like we were trying to harm you.

283
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:01,200
Now, you want to learn more.

284
00:17:01,390 --> 00:17:02,630
I've taught you all the techniques

